We want you to be healthy, balanced, and feel secure. That’s why you’ll enjoy a comprehensive range of benefits, with a focus on supporting your whole health. Starting on day one of your employment, you’ll be offered several health-related benefits including medical, vision, dental, and well-being and behavioral health programs. We also offer a retirement program, 401(k) with company match, company paid life insurance, tuition reimbursement and a minimum of 18 days of paid time off per year.


PSEG offers a unique experience to our more than 12,000 employees – we provide the resources and opportunities for career development that come with being a Fortune 500 company, as well as the attention, camaraderie and care for one another you might typically associate with a small business. Our focus on combatting climate change through clean energy technology, our new net zero climate vision for 2030 and enhanced commitment to diversity, equity and inclusion; and supporting the communities we serve make this a particularly exciting time to join PSEG.


**Job Summary**
---------------


This position is the Paralegal for – and a critical member of – the Labor, Employment & Benefits legal team at PSEG, providing key support for matters of significance to the enterprise relating to the employer/employee relationship.


**Job Responsibilities**
------------------------

**Responsibilities include:**  

* Coordinate all aspects of discovery relating to litigation, arbitrations and agency charges involving current and former employees, taking the lead on gathering necessary information and documents;
* Oversee e-discovery for employment law matters, including making recommendations for custodian data collection and search criteria, reviewing results and tagging for relevancy;
* Coordinate, track and project manage tasks relating to Company-sponsored immigration matters;
* Draft legal hold notices;
* Index and summarize documents and information;
* Assist with witness interviews and preparation for depositions;
* Appropriately handle all subpoenas received by the Company relating to employment and/or benefit records;
* Attend Employee Benefits Committee and Employee Benefits Sub-Committee meetings to take notes and prepare minutes;
* Draft response letters to benefits claimants based on the Committees’ adjudication of appeals;
* Maintain detailed appeal tracking chart for Corporate Benefits;
* Respond to external and internal audit requests;
* Project manage immigration matters, coordinating between outside counsel and internal stakeholders and ensuring all deadlines are met and required files maintained;
* Organize and maintain records, files and information related to practice group matters, preparing and updating reports as needed; and
* Perform any other duties as assigned.
**Job Specific Qualifications**
-------------------------------

**Required Qualifications and Competencies:**  

* 3+ years of paralegal experience at a law firm or in house legal department;
* Advanced Microsoft Office skills;
* Excellent verbal and written communication skills;
* Ability to work under pressure, handling and appropriately prioritizing multiple tasks;
* Strong planning and organizational skills;
* Ability to interact professionally with internal clients, attorneys, retained counsel, other paralegals, and administrative assistants
* Understanding of proper management, handling and storage of confidential files and documents;
* Ability to perform legal research using Internet based research tools including Westlaw;
* Ability to work independently with minimal day-to-day oversight;
* Team player able to work collaboratively across practice and department lines;
* Must foster an inclusive work environment and respect all aspects of diversity; and
* Must demonstrate and value differences in others’ strengths, perspectives, approaches, and personal choices.
**Desired Qualifications and Competencies:**  

* College degree or some college level courses;
* Paralegal Certificate;
* Significant experience handling employment law matters at a law firm or in house legal department;
* Experience responding to subpoenas;
* Experience investigating and drafting responses to charges filed with the EEOC and similar state/local agencies; and
* Familiarity with employee benefit plans and benefit claims.
